<TITLE> 3 ETV crew hurt in Khaleda motorcade crash </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Reazul Bashar bdnews24.com correspondent Dhaka, Dec 17 (bdnews24.com)  Three crew of a private TV station, who were following BNP chairperson Khaleda Zia's motorcade, were injured when their microbus was hit by a bus in Sirajganj on Wednesday. Special correspondent Rashed Ahmed, cameraman Asaduzzaman Asad and driver Rabiul Islam of Ekushey Television were rushed to Chandaikona Hospital. They were later moved to Bogra Ziaur Rahman Medical College Hospital. The accident occurred shortly after 1pm at Bhuiyangati under Raiganj Upazila in Sirajganj when the oncoming passenger bus, Salma Classic Paribahan, on Dhaka-Joypurhat-Hili route, hit the microbus. The bus also fell into the roadside ditch, but no reports of injuries were immediately available. Khaleda was out on Wednesday for another two-day visit to take her election campaign to the northern region. The former prime minister left Dhaka in a motorcade at around 10am. She will address 28 public gatherings in 13 districts during the trip, with the first at Sherpur in Bogra. b
